WEBVTT

00:00.770 --> 00:04.315
Hello friends, I'm Rick Warren, and welcome to Spurgeon's Sermons.

00:04.775 --> 00:09.522
This is the official podcast brought to you by Premier and Spurgeon's College.

00:10.182 --> 00:18.353
You know the teachings of Charles Spurgeon have had a personal impact on my life in a profound way, and I'm confident they'll do the same for you.

00:18.473 --> 00:27.986
So get ready to be challenged, equipped, and guided by Charles Spurgeon, who is universally regarded as the greatest English preacher in the history of the church.

00:29.602 --> 00:35.189
The heroic in Christianity, a sermon by Charles Spurgeon, part one.

00:36.510 --> 00:40.395
For if ye love them which love you, what thank have ye?

00:40.455 --> 00:43.839
For sinners also love those that love them.

00:43.879 --> 00:49.887
And if ye do good to them which do good to you, what thank have ye?

00:49.947 --> 00:52.710
For sinners also do even the same.

00:53.892 --> 00:59.218
And if ye lend to them of whom ye hope to receive, what thank have ye?

01:00.098 --> 01:04.384
For sinners also lend to sinners to receive as much again.

01:05.426 --> 01:09.872
Luke's Gospel, chapter 6, verses 32 to 34.

01:12.496 --> 01:18.845
Brethren in Christ, every word which proceeds out of our master's lips is precious to us.

01:19.867 --> 01:27.698
We make no distinction between his promises and his precepts, but prize every syllable above rubies.

01:28.834 --> 01:37.322
A doctrine from him, we value beyond much fine gold, and a command is equally high in our esteem.

01:38.443 --> 01:48.654
Whether his teaching be practical or doctrinal, whether it be intended to guide the feet or to encourage the heart, we are equally rejoiced at it.

01:49.935 --> 01:57.202
All his words are music, though they make us weep, infinitely tender, infinitely deep.

01:58.946 --> 02:10.744
All the discourses of Jesus are the words of God to our soul, whether they convey to us instruction, warning, rebuke, invitation, or consolation.

02:12.126 --> 02:21.821
As all His garments smell of mer and aloes and cassia, so are all His words most sweet to our taste.

02:23.143 --> 02:25.266
We have not so learned Christ

02:25.506 --> 02:29.390
as to be pickers and choosers when the fruits of his lips are before us.

02:30.592 --> 02:42.486
Yet have I known professing Christians of that sort, who would feign rend the master's clothes, that they might have only the softest part of it to be a pillow for their idle heads?

02:43.707 --> 02:53.298
That, they say, was a gospel sermon, sweet food for our souls, because it happened to tell of what Christ has done for us.

02:54.434 --> 02:59.900
But on the next occasion they cry out, that was not a gospel sermon, it was legal.

03:00.481 --> 03:07.828
It laid a burden upon our shoulders, because it dared to tell of what Christ has commanded us to do for Him.

03:08.950 --> 03:14.876
Such people, it seems to me, accept Christ for a servant rather than for a master.

03:15.977 --> 03:24.146
They are glad that He shall do this or that for them, that He shall in fact gird Himself and wait at their table

03:24.354 --> 03:25.996
while they sit down to meet.

03:27.117 --> 03:41.931
But if they had learned better, they would have chosen Christ for a master and would have been willing to gird themselves at His command and wait on their Lord, counting it their honor to be servants of so divine a prince.

03:43.132 --> 03:53.202
Feeling certain that you are not of that order of religious complainers, but that you will accept anything that comes from Christ, I am glad

03:53.346 --> 03:55.810
to have a practical subject this morning.

03:57.092 --> 04:03.101
The Sermon on the Mount is as full of light to you as the transfiguration on the Mount.

04:03.922 --> 04:14.037
You are as glad to hear what the Son of God has to say by way of precept as to hear what the Father had to say by way of recognition of His Son.

04:15.399 --> 04:22.930
As for this Sermon in the plain, it was preceded by miracles, but it is as forcible to you

04:23.234 --> 04:27.260
as the signs and wonders could have made it, had you seen them all.

04:28.782 --> 04:35.432
The sick touched his garment and were restored, and those who were possessed of devils were healed.

04:36.453 --> 04:50.994
You rejoice at the miracles of Christ, but you see him to be as mighty in word as indeed, and you adore him for his gracious teachings, which remain to us after his miracles have ceased.

04:52.066 --> 04:58.193
Here you have certain of the words of Christ, and may his Spirit bless them to your hearts.

05:00.015 --> 05:16.833
Brethren, in the matters of which I shall have to speak this morning in the name of the Lord, taken as I am quite certain from his own words, there will be some things strange and unusual which may possibly sound harshly in your ears.

05:17.955 --> 05:19.036
Be not astonished.

05:19.997 --> 05:21.138
For the gospel

05:21.250 --> 05:25.094
is one of those thoughts of God which are not our thoughts.

05:26.275 --> 05:36.065
The whole system which Christ has ushered in is foreign to men, being as far above them as the heavens are above the earth.

05:37.466 --> 05:39.909
Our Lord's kingdom is not of this world.

05:40.750 --> 05:44.814
Else would His servants do many things which now they forbear to do.

05:46.596 --> 05:48.978
The conduct of the subjects of that kingdom

05:49.378 --> 05:52.001
must not be measured by the manners of others.

05:52.862 --> 05:56.826
For they are a people as peculiar as the kingdom to which they belong.

05:57.787 --> 06:03.494
We have heard persons say, I do not see it to be my duty to be so precise.

06:04.334 --> 06:05.636
It is not customary.

06:06.697 --> 06:09.200
What have you and I to do with custom?

06:10.361 --> 06:15.146
If things are right, but not in fashion, let us start the fashion.

06:16.188 --> 06:18.450
And when it is the fashion to do wrong,

06:18.914 --> 06:21.657
Let us be desperately unfashionable.

06:22.959 --> 06:37.274
Our master evidently from the verses before us did not come into the world to teach us to conform to the ways of our fellow men, but he would have us go far beyond the ordinary conduct of our fellows.

06:38.696 --> 06:44.082
He asked in his sermon on the Mount, what do ye more than others?

06:45.122 --> 06:49.910
He ordains a standard far above the common standard of mankind.

06:50.451 --> 06:54.318
When he says again and again, what thank have ye?

06:54.378 --> 06:57.984
For sinners also do even the same.

06:59.707 --> 07:07.841
Oh, one may say at the close of my sermon, the preacher demands more of us than can reasonably be expected from flesh and blood.

07:09.264 --> 07:10.706
Your charge is correct.

07:11.970 --> 07:24.726
But then the preacher is not addressing himself to you as to flesh and blood, but as to those who are possessed of a far higher principle, namely the indwelling Spirit of God.

07:26.328 --> 07:41.426
True believers walk not after the flesh, nor do they mind the things of it, for they are clothed with the energy of the Spirit of God, and by his power, their lives are lifted above the common walks of men.

07:42.658 --> 07:49.907
if so be, that the Spirit of God dwelleth in you ye are of another nature than the men of this world.

07:51.069 --> 07:55.975
And it is to be expected that ye should live after a nobler fashion.

07:57.497 --> 08:03.465
What manner of persons ought ye to be in all holy conversation and godliness?

08:04.766 --> 08:10.674
We live under a spirit whose law is perfection, and therefore a little fault

08:11.170 --> 08:13.653
causes us much self-condemnation.

08:14.875 --> 08:19.320
We judge ourselves by a more severe rule than we would apply to others.

08:20.362 --> 08:26.850
For our privileges and responsibilities are exceptionally great.

08:26.870 --> 08:30.615
I allow in other men what I would denounce in myself.

08:32.036 --> 08:39.666
I could approve in some men actions which to me also would be lawful but would not be expedient.

08:40.226 --> 08:44.511
upon the higher rule of glorifying God in all things.

08:46.133 --> 09:00.971
When I have heard of certain deeds of unconverted and unenlightened men, I have excused them, saying poor souls, considering who they were, and where they were, their conduct is not so heavily to be blamed.

09:02.193 --> 09:09.842
And yet if I had behaved one half as badly, there would have been rebellion and presumption in the deed.

09:10.594 --> 09:16.143
For favoured children, there is a different law from that which governs common subjects.

09:17.124 --> 09:22.933
That which is passed over in strangers is atrocious when it comes from a close friend.

09:24.075 --> 09:27.079
You are not under law, but under grace.

09:28.221 --> 09:36.594
And being under grace, you feel the force of a constraint even holier and higher than mere law could put upon you.

09:38.498 --> 09:59.388
If you are what you profess to be, my brethren, more is expected from you than from any other people beneath the sun, and therefore I shall throw aside all hesitancy in setting before you a supreme standard and asking of you what we never can get from sinners nor from people of the world.

10:00.970 --> 10:03.474
Do you not know that your Lord has said

10:03.842 --> 10:09.109
except your righteousness shall exceed the righteousness of the scribes and Pharisees.

10:09.810 --> 10:13.114
He shall in no case enter the kingdom of heaven.

10:15.117 --> 10:26.272
If I were called to address an ordinary company of men and women upon feats of valor, I might speak with baited breath if I exhorted them to heroism in war.

10:27.794 --> 10:33.842
But if I had lived some thousands of years ago and had been called upon to talk to Spartan warriors,

10:34.082 --> 10:39.890
All equipped for battle, men graved and scored with the scars of conflict.

10:40.751 --> 10:43.595
I should set no bounds to my exhortations.

10:44.256 --> 10:50.444
I would bestow them as a lion, arouses the young lions, and urges them to the prey.

10:51.666 --> 11:03.442
I should tell them that their name and parentage should not be disgraced by the idea of defeat, but that they must expect victory and seize it as their right.

11:04.162 --> 11:07.927
No orator would have spoken to Spartans as to be oceans.

11:08.608 --> 11:14.916
It was their very life and business to fight, and deeds of prowess were therefore to be looked for from them.

11:16.438 --> 11:17.560
Is it not so with you?

11:18.020 --> 11:19.783
You followers of the crucified.

11:21.004 --> 11:27.693
Your martyrs and confessors call upon you to lead a life beyond that of common men and women.

11:29.115 --> 11:34.162
I say all this because to certain of you a sort of apology may seem needful.

11:34.498 --> 11:37.982
for the strong things that may be said before you at this time.

11:39.163 --> 11:49.334
May God's Holy Spirit come upon you and make you strong enough for all the strong things, glorifying Himself in your weakness.

11:50.395 --> 11:51.677
Thank you for listening, friends.

11:51.957 --> 11:57.303
